regulation was desirable. Half of them agreed that there should be some kind
of system to licence approved trainers.
The society describes the concern over training quality as 'alarming'. But
it does not support a licensing system, which it says might be bureaucratic.
Instead, it calls for training bodies to draw up agreed criteria to help
employers judge the effectiveness of trainers.
