The new Glyndebourne Opera House was unveiled yesterday amid claims that it
is the first professional opera house built in the UK since Glyndebourne
opened 60 years ago. The Pounds 33.5m auditorium, designed by architects
Michael Hopkins &amp; Partners, and constructed in less than 18 months. It
occupies the site of the old theatre in Sussex. The new theatre on four
levels has a total capacity of 1,200, with 370 more seats than the old one.
