FT  01 FEB 94 / German machine tool industry shows some sign of growth
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JUDY DEMPSEY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BERLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Germany's machine tool industry, one of the key sectors reflecting trends in
the country's economy, is showing some sign of growth, the association for
German machine tool manufacturers, VDMA, said yesterday, writes Judy Dempsey
from Berlin.
Foreign orders in December rose by 19 per cent compared with the same period
the previous year, although there were few signs that orders from European
Union countries and eastern Europe were increasing. The VDMA said that
south-east Asia, the US and Latin America accounted for the bulk of the
orders.
But domestic orders continued to decrease in December, falling by 14 per
cent over the same period last year.
