Sir William has opted to present the results in Hong Kong, leaving the
honours in London to John Bond, chief executive. All perfectly proper, given
that HSBC has a slightly higher capitalisation on the Hong Kong exchange
than in London. But perhaps rather telling about the city in which he feels
most comfortable, central bank formalities aside.
