FT  31 JAN 94 / Gains for Taiwan opposition
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Taiwan's governing Nationalist party has won local government elections but
the main opposition Democratic Progressive party (DPP) and independent
candidates made strong gains, Reuter reports from Taipei.
The Nationalists won 214 of 309 village and town mayoral posts at stake in
Saturday's polls, which were marred by allegations of vote-buying and
campaign violence. They won 260 mayoral posts in the last elections, in
1990. The DPP more than tripled its number of mayoral seats to 21 from six.
The polls will not alter the balance of power in central government.
